      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/1/30/3",
      "text": [
        " رَجُلٍ شَهِدَ عَلَى شَهَادَةِ رَجُلٍ فَجَاءَ اَلرَّجُلُ فَقَالَ إِنِّي لَمْ أُشْهِدْهُ قَالَ \"تَجُوزُ شَهَادَةُ أَعْدَلِهِمَا وَ إِنْ كَانَتْ عَدَالَتُهُمَا وَاحِدَةً لَمْ تَجُزْ شَهَادَتُهُ \"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.3353 - It is narrated from Abdullah ibn Sinan, from Abdurrahman ibn Abi Abdullah, from Abu Abdullah (as) regarding a man who testified based on the testimony of another man, and then the original man said: 'I did not make him a witness,'\nImam (as) said: \"The testimony of the more upright of the two is accepted, but if their uprightness is equal, then his testimony is not accepted.\""
        ]
      }
    },
